# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# FoodBall environment template.  Copy to .env.local and fill in.
# RULE (NIST IA-5 / SOC2 CC6.1): the FRONTEND may ONLY ever see the Supabase
# anon key + URL. The service-role key and the football-data token are SERVER
# secrets — never put them in a VITE_* variable (those are bundled into the
# client and are publicly visible).
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

# --- Frontend (safe to ship to the browser) -------------------------------
# The anon key is a public, RLS-gated key. RLS is what protects the data.
VITE_SUPABASE_URL=https://YOUR-PROJECT.supabase.co
VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key

# For local Docker run against the bundled Postgres proof harness, the SPA has
# no live Supabase to talk to; auth/data require either hosted Supabase or the
# Supabase CLI stack (see docs/RUNNING.md). When using the CLI stack locally:
# VITE_SUPABASE_URL=http://127.0.0.1:54321
# VITE_SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=<printed by `npx supabase start`>

# --- Server-only secrets (NEVER prefixed VITE_; loaded from files in prod) --
# Supabase service-role key — used only by the seed script / Edge Functions.
SUPABASE_SERVICE_ROLE_KEY=your-service-role-key
# football-data.org API token — stored as a Supabase secret, not in the client.
FOOTBALL_DATA_TOKEN=your-football-data-token
# Edge Function (sync-fixtures) cron auth — a shared secret for pg_cron calls.
SYNC_SECRET=generate-a-long-random-string

# --- Self-host backend (GoTrue SMTP for password resets) --------------------
# The Gmail/Workspace app password is read from secrets/smtp_password.txt at
# go-live and exported as GOTRUE_SMTP_PASS — NEVER commit it. See docs/DEPLOYMENT.md.
# GOTRUE_SMTP_PASS=loaded-from-secrets/smtp_password.txt
